ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would recommend this course to another student. If you are interested in doing qualitative research in your future, or even just want a better understanding of how to assess qualitative research, this is really a good course to take. I was able to spend the semester designing my own project, which I hope to complete in the near future, and getting hands-on experience of how to do qualitative research.
Yes, because this class allows students to learn about qualitative research method and provides opportunity to practice use it through a guided student project.
Comprehensive overview of qualitative analysis focused on helping you to further define you dissertation topic
Yes- see answer to question 1. Only downside- might have liked a little more guidance/structure and more on grounded theory and thematic analysis.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: I won't be doing a dissertation, but I feel like this course gave me a much broader understanding of the research that's out there and how to utilize different methodologies to answer whatever research questions I come up with in the future.
Give me the option to consider a qualitative nursing study myself in the future and to equip with basis qualitativedata analysis skills.
Helped me gain additional clarity on my dissertation topic
I may want to do qualitative or mixed methods for my dissertation. In that regard this class was very helpful. I did not have any experience with qual research prior to taking this class.
